chrome_omnibox

Top-Level Variables
omnibox: ChromeOmnibox
Classes
ChromeOmnibox

The omnibox API allows you to register a keyword with Google Chrome's address bar, which is also known as the omnibox.

Top-Level Variables

static final ChromeOmnibox omnibox

Fields

Getters and Setters

Stream<dynamic> get onInputCancelled

User has ended the keyword input session without accepting the input.

Stream<dynamic> get onInputChanged

User has changed what is typed into the omnibox.

Stream<dynamic> get onInputEntered

User has accepted what is typed into the omnibox.

Stream<dynamic> get onInputStarted

User has started a keyword input session by typing the extension's keyword. This is guaranteed to be sent exactly once per input session, and before any onInputChanged events.

Methods

void sendSuggestions(int requestId, dynamic suggestResults)

A callback passed to the onInputChanged event used for sending suggestions back to the browser.

suggestResults An array of suggest results

void setDefaultSuggestion(dynamic suggestion)

Sets the description and styling for the default suggestion. The default suggestion is the text that is displayed in the first suggestion row underneath the URL bar. suggestion A partial SuggestResult object, without the 'content' parameter.
